  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): 0.3.8+commit.7ff8f307\r\n* OS: OSX\r\n* Python Version (output of `python --version`): 3.8.0\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nConverting a `String` `a`  into a `bool` is allowed but it performs the following `slot_number(a) != 0`\r\n \r\nFor example, a call to `foo` will return `True` here, but if we were to comment the first line, it would return `False` as `a` is now at slot 0 of the storage:\r\n\r\n```Vyper\r\nb:uint256\r\na: String[1]\r\n@external\r\n@payable\r\ndef foo() -> bool:\r\n    g:bool = convert(self.a, bool)\r\n    return g\r\n```\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nConversion from `String` to `bool` should maybe be blocked as it doesn't really make sense anyway.",
